    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName><add>?</add> Bay</placeName>
                <date>21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> April 1857</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>. &amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Rev Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I hope you will pardon the liberty I take in this<lb/> trespassing
                upon your valuable time and attention to claim regard<lb/> for the affairs of an
                individual who has not the honor to be known<lb/> to you. Your prominent position
                among our Brethren in <placeName>America</placeName>, &amp;<lb/> your reputed zeal
                in Jewish affairs generally have emboldened me<lb/> to address you &amp; made me
                confident that you will forgive my pardon<lb/> in consideration of the nature of my
                communication.</p>
            <p>I have had the honor to preside over the congregation Beth Ya<add>?</add> of<lb/>
                this place for several years &amp; during that time of ministry, it has been<lb/> my
                good fortune to possess the respect &amp; esteem of all classes of my
                constituents.<lb/> Unhappily, the depression of affairs in the
                    <placeName>island</placeName> generally, has extend<lb/>-ed its influence into
                our holy institution &amp; its diminished resources have<lb/> forced the rulers to
                retrench its expenditure commensurately with the times.<lb/> I have thus with an
                increasing family been subjected to a diminution<lb/> of a stipend never more than
                adequate to a respectable living. Unfortu-<lb/>-nately this is too limited a sphere
                &amp; furnishes no opportunity to improve<lb/> my circumstances by any employment
                reconcilable with the dis-<lb/>-tinguished profession, of which I am an humble
                member. The<lb/> Jewish children of the community do not amount to six—all<lb/>
                attempts at book making &amp; class teaching &amp;c have proved <add>?</add></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>&amp; then it is that although I otherwise enjoy an enviable lot in the<lb/>
                possession of a prize in the usually poor lottery of Jewish ministry,<lb/> I am
                forced to sacrifice it, for the welfare of my family.</p>
            <p>In my search after some advantageous change, I direct myself to<lb/> you,
                    with<add>?</add> the promises that my desires are limited within the
                boundaries<lb/> of a respectable living, I respectfully solicit any information you
                may<lb/> possess concerning those congregations in <placeName>America</placeName>
                who may be in need of<lb/> ministers. If to this, you will be good enough to add a
                few words of<lb/> counsel, the favor will be considerably enhanced. It might be<lb/>
                as well to state that I have received what is termed a liberal<lb/> education—am
                accustomed frequently to disperse instruction from<lb/> the pulpit &amp; possess
                professional credentials from the <persName>Revd Dr Meldola</persName><lb/> Hazan
                    <persName>De Sola</persName> &amp;c &amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In conclusion, I beg to refer you to the <persName>Revd M N
                    Nathan</persName><lb/> of <placeName>New Orleans</placeName> &amp; the
                    <persName>Revd Abm DeSola</persName> of <placeName>Montreal</placeName>, who
                will as-<lb/>suredly vouch for my <hi rend="underline">principle</hi> &amp; convince
                you that your good<lb/>-ness will not be un<add>?</add>
                <add>?</add> up.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Your very obliged servant</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">A P Mendes</persName>
            </p>
            <p>PS.</p>
            <p>The congregation of <placeName>Richmond Va</placeName></p>
            <p>has been especially pointed out to me.</p>
            <p>May I solicit your advice?</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">APM.</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
